Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_flexfil...route_blockage(25.10)  create_flexfil...route_blockage(25.10)

Name
       create_flexfiller_route_blockage  -  Generates default congestion model
       to estimate routing blockages over FlexFillers based on  user-specified
       percentage value for characterizing

Syntax
       create_flexfiller_route_blockage

       [-help]

       Generates  default  congestion model to estimate routing blockages over
       FlexFillers based on user-specified percentage value  for  characteriz-
       ing.   This  command  can  handle both module-based and instance group-
       based FlexModels. Routing blockage value  of  an  instance  group-based
       FlexModels  will be derived based on its parent module routing blockage
       value. You should run this command when models are already created.

       Note: This command should be used for Active-logic Reduction  technique
       (ART)  based  model generation flow. For non ART based flow, congestion
       model can be created during create_proto_model command.

       Note: The FlexFillers generation capability supports  hybrid  rows  and
       generates  FlexFillers  that  can  fit in the floorplan rows and can be
       placed legally in the floorplan.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each create_flexfiller_route_blockage parameter.
              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command: man create_flexfiller_route_blockage.

       Examples

              * The  following  example  indicates  that 10% of created models
                will be used for routing blockage characterization:

                create_flexfiller_route_blockage

              * The following example indicates that 80% of created flexmodels
                will  be  used  for  routing  blockage  characterization   and
                tdsp_core and alu modules should be part of these 80% models:

                set_proto_mode -include_model_route_blockage {tdsp_core alu}

                set_proto_mode -characterize_percent_rt_blockage 0.8

                create_flexfiller_route_blockage

              *

                Begin pinDensity

                # model_name pin_density flag

                #  If  flag is 1, use place_design and earlyGlobalRoute result
                for pin density.

                # If flat is 0, tool auto calculate it based on the  pin  area
                and total instance area.

                MOUT_DT_CTL 1.952371 1

                ZRAS_RZ 2.361781 0

                End pinDensity

